content.description: Start with a good left and a bad right undercling. Make moves on crimps and set up for either a large throw, or some more crimps to gain a good jug. Another large move gains you the jug just below the lip and a fairly casual top out.
content.protection: A good number of pads and spotters at the landing slopes away slightly and the climb is fairly tall.
content.location: On the northwest face of the Silverback boulder.

content.description: Start matched on a good left facing J-shaped jug. Make a few tricky moves out and slightly left to gain the lip. Continue left on holds at the lip until you gain a massive left hand jug and roll over the top. You could probably top out straight out from the start, but it looks extremely chossy.
content.location: Starts to the right of silverback.

content.description: This area is located at the very top of East Mountain. One of those most aesthetic boulders in the park. Gets afternoon sun and morning shade.
